{"timestamp": "2025-12-05 18:49:03.488404", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Solution submitted.\n\nSummary of submission:\n- is_anomaly: true\n- faulty_devices: [\"dhcp_server\"]\n- root_cause_name: [\"dhcp_service_down\"]\n\nRecommended next actions (optional, not submitted):\n- Start/enable isc-dhcp-server on dhcp_server (systemctl start --now isc-dhcp-server; systemctl enable isc-dhcp-server).\n- Check DHCP server logs (/var/log/syslog or journalctl -u isc-dhcp-server) and /var/lib/dhcp/dhcpd.leases for errors and active leases.\n- Verify dhcpd config for correct subnet declarations and authoritative setting.\n- After service restored, either wait for clients to renew or trigger DHCP renew (dhclient) on representative hosts, or reboot/renew to reacquire addresses.\n- Optionally investigate intermittent 50% ICMP loss separately if it persists after DHCP restoration.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 2245, "output_tokens": 180, "total_tokens": 2425, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 2176}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 0}}}
